  m_Name: Humerus_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Humerus_L
  partName: Humerus left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left humerus is a long bone located in the upper portion of the canine left
    forelimb, connecting the shoulder to the elbow. It forms articulations with the
    scapula, radius, and ulna, enabling coordinated movement and weight-bearing during
    locomotion. This bone contains important attachment
  - sites for muscles responsible for flexion, extension, and stabilization of the
    forelimb. The humerus plays a major role in transmitting forces generated during
    running, jumping, and standing activities. Its structural design supports both
    mobility and strength while maintaining joint alignment.
